100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 7, 1926, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, tackling issues of international security and economic cooperation in the post-war era. In the United States, President Calvin Coolidge addressed the nation, emphasizing the importance of economic stability amid ongoing debates over Prohibition. Meanwhile, in Europe, the political landscape shifted as various nations grappled with the aftermath of the Great War and the rise of new ideologies.
